ients.', '$50M-$150M', 'medium', 'low', 'Marine research institutions, environmental agencies, coastal tourism boards, water sports companies, and climate monitoring organizations', 3, '["Subscription-based service providing weekly/monthly documented reports to multiple research clients", "Contract work with environmental agencies for specific research projects or seasonal monitoring", "Data licensing model selling standardized footage/observations to multiple commercial users"]', NULL, '["Low revenue ceiling ($450/mo suggests limited market willingness to pay) restricts scalability", "Geographic limitation to coastal areas reduces addressable market size", "Commodity-like service vulnerable to automation (buoys, drones, automated cameras) replacing manual observation"]', '["Identify and directly contact 10-15 potential customer segments (research institutions, tourism boards, environmental NGOs) to validate willingness to pay and specific data requirements", "Research existing automated monitoring solutions to understand the competitive landscape and identify defensible differentiation", "Develop a minimum viable service with one client to establish operational feasibility, cost structure, and realistic revenue potential"]', NULL, 'Marine research institutions, environmental agencies, and coastal businesses lack cost-effective mechanisms for consistent, reliable documentation of oceanic conditions. Current solutions rely on expensive automated monitoring systems or sporadic manual observations, creating a gap for affordable, flexible data collection services.', NULL, 37.7786, -122.4892, NULL, NULL, NULL) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
